    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-20T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-20T23:00:00-05:00" n="439"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/959c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-21T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 21, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>669. Reference Department’s 668 of June 21.<note n="6" xml:id="d439fn6">Not
                        printed.</note> It is the consensus of the interested American republics
                    that the Bolivian regime be recognized on June 23.</p>
                <p>Please deliver to the Foreign Minister at 11 a.m. on that date a note stating as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have the honor to advise Your Excellency that my Government, having
                            full confidence that Your Excellency’s Government will dedicate itself
                            to complete and effective implementation of its announced friendly
                            attitude toward the cause of the United Nations in the present war
                            effort, is pleased to extend, as of this date, full recognition to Your
                            Excellency’s Government. Accept, etc.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>At the hour mentioned above the Department will release a statement to the
                        press.<note n="7" xml:id="d439fn7">Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bulletin</hi>, June 24, 1944, p. 584.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
